<br>
but there's things that need to be said about this.<br>
<br>
<br>
1) Boofy can be hard to deal with some times, I'll give you that, but who here hasn't had their bad days.<br>
<br>
2) Boofy has done some things that wouldn't be acceptable in the game. But who here hasn't done that...kill stolen a monster that you were positive was yours...etc..<br>
<br>
But who here has tried to go back....on the chat boards, IN THE PUBLIC chat boards, and Openly said he was sorry. That he doesn't like the way things have gone, and he's ready to change.<br>
<br>
You guild is killing their reputation because a few of your members are flaming a person that's apologizing.<br>
<br>
Saying what goes around comes around is good advice, you should take it. Because some day you'll end up in the same situation, and i'm sure you won't want someone being an ass when your trying to apologize.<br>
<br>
Boofy can be a really cool person if you get to know him. I should know....Boofy and I hated each other in Junior high, and it wasn't till Sophmore year of high school did we become best friends.<br>
<br>
&quot;The important thing is not to take people seriously on the flame boards.&quot;<br>
<br>
I know it's difficult...people try to degrade you, and cuss at you, and do anything to make you mad, or hurt your reputation.<br>
<br>
But the fact is, that person's angry...and the Play nice polocy makes it to where they can't vent their frustration in the game, so they have to take it out somewhere else. That place is the flame boards.<br>
<br>
Some people get a kick out of reading them, and responding to them....hense boofy and myself. <br>
<br>
Some people take it to personal...<br>
<br>
I will talk to boofy personally about posting on the flame board to make sure this doesn't happen again. In the mean time, I want the people who posted in that post to think about how they could have handled themselves better...<br>
<br>
By this I mean:<br>
<br>
&quot;why are you flaming someone who wants to make up?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;are you trying to keep him your enemy?&quot;<br>
<br>
And I know some of you are going to say...It was just a post, you shouldn't take it so personal. The fact is, I take it personal when someone is getting flamed for trying to apologize.<br>
<br>
I believe that everyone should get a second chance...<br>
<br>
cause i'm sure you'd want the same thing if you were in his/her situation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udoofyrainbowfloatar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Doofy Rainbowfloatar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 476<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/01 11:13:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   oh...</span><hr size=1> by the way...I didn't bother to spell check. <br>
